Preconditions:
The input parameter `n` is a positive integer representing the number of cities.
The input parameter `roads` is a 2D array representing the roads between cities. Each element in the array is an array of two integers representing the cities connected by the road.
The roads array is not null and contains valid city indices.
The destination city is one of the cities in the input.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer representing the number of ways to arrive at the destination city in the shortest amount of time.
The returned value is the count of all possible paths from the starting city to the destination city.
The returned value is calculated modulo 10^9 + 7 to handle large results.